org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector

Interface OutputSelector<OUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    OUT - Type parameter of the split values.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IterateExample.MySelector

    public interface OutputSelector<OUT>
extends Serializable
    Interface for defining an OutputSelector for a SplitDataStream using the SingleOutputStreamOperator.split(org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector.OutputSelector<OUT>) call. Every output object of a SplitDataStream will run through this operator to select outputs.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Iterable<String> select(OUT value)
      Method for selecting output names for the emitted objects when using the SingleOutputStreamOperator.split(org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector.OutputSelector<OUT>) method.

    • Method Detail

      • select

        Iterable<String> select(OUT value)
        Method for selecting output names for the emitted objects when using the SingleOutputStreamOperator.split(org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector.OutputSelector<OUT>) method. The values will be emitted only to output names which are contained in the returned iterable.
        Parameters:
        value - Output object for which the output selection should be made.
